solutions.content:
# Intuition
The basic rule of Parenthesis matching  at each point is 
- While traversing from left to right count(leftParenthesis)> count(rightParenthesis). Then at the end of traversal, we can check if left==right.
- While traversing from right to left count(rightParenthesis)> count(leftParenthesis). Then at the end of traversal, we can check if left==right.

# Approach
- The problem is similar to normal parenthesis matching just that we have extra paramater as "*" which can either be a left parenthesis or a right parenthesis or empty string.
- So we will traverse the string 2 times, one from left hand side to check that any point we do not have rightParenthesis > leftParenthesis.
Then we will traverse from right to left, to check that at any point we do not have leftParenthesis > rightParenthesis.
- So we have extra "*", which can be anything, so while traversing left to right we can add a check that if rightParenthesis > leftParenthesis + star, that means return false.
If it did not return false until the end of traversal we just need to check if  left+star>=right as star can have empty value as well.
- Similarly while traversing right to left we can add a check that if leftParenthesis > rightParenthesis + star, that means return false.
If it did not return false until the end of traversal we just need to check if  right+star>=left as star can have empty value as well.



# Complexity
- **Time complexity**:
We are traversing the loop twice so O(2n)-->O(n)

- **Space complexity**:
We are not utilising any extra space. SC O(1).

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkValidString(string s) {
        int l=0,r=0;
        int star=0;
        for(auto it:s)
        {
            if(it=='(')l++;
            else if(it==')')r++;
            else star++;
            if(r>l+star)return false;
        }
        bool f1= (l+star>=r);
        l=0;
        r=0;
        star=0;
        for(int i=s.size()-1;i>=0;i--)
        {
            if(s[i]=='(')l++;
            else if(s[i]==')')r++;
            else star++;

            if(l>r+star)return false;
        }
        bool f2=(r+star>=l);
        return (f1 and f2);
    }
};
```

