# Greedy solution
* If open paren '('  - then push to **leftParenIndices** stack
* If '\*' - then push to **starIndices** stack
* If close paren ')' then,
	* if **leftParenIndices** stack is not Empty then match it, else
	* if **starIndices** stack is not empty then match it, else
	* No matching present return **false**

*  Once All closing paren is matched - if **leftParenIndices** stack is not empty then,
	*  if **starIndices** is not empty then check whether the * is after left paren '('
	*  if either **starIndices** is empty or the index falls before '(' then return **false**

```
public boolean checkValidString(String s) {
        Stack<Integer> leftParenIndices = new Stack<>();
        Stack<Integer> starIndices = new Stack<>();

        for (int index = 0; index < s.length(); index++) {
            char c = s.charAt(index);
            if (c == '(') leftParenIndices.push(index);
            else if (c == ')') {
                if (!leftParenIndices.isEmpty()) leftParenIndices.pop();
                else if (!starIndices.isEmpty()) starIndices.pop();
                else return false;
            } else {
                starIndices.push(index);
            }
        }

        while (!leftParenIndices.isEmpty()) {
            if (starIndices.isEmpty() || starIndices.pop() < leftParenIndices.pop()) return false;
        }

        return true;
    }
```

