solutions.content:
In this solution we traverse the string twice, once from left to right and once from left to right.

In each pass we check four things :
1. Number of Stars.
2. Number of open brackets
3. Number of closed brackets
4. Unpaired brackets (closed - open)

After each step we check whether the **number of unpaired is greater than the stars or not**.
If yes we there and then return FALSE. (as we can't proceed after that)
otherwise we continue. 
If we are able traverse the string through both passes then we return TRUE.

It is a clever way to solve this problem.

Happy Coding :-)


```
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkValidString(string s) {       


        int star = 0, open = 0, closed = 0, unpaired;
        for(int i = 0; i <s.length(); i++) {
            if (s[i] == '*')
                star++;
            else if (s[i] == '(')
                open++;
            else if (s[i] == ')')
                closed++;
            unpaired = closed-open;
            if (unpaired > star)
                return false;
        }

        star = 0, open = 0, closed = 0, unpaired=0;
        for(int i = s.length() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (s[i] == '*')
                star++;
            else if (s[i] == '(')
                open++;
            else if (s[i] == ')')
                closed++;
            unpaired = open-closed;
            if (unpaired > star)
                return false;
        }

        return true;
    }
};
