So the main problem in this question is to determine weather to take '*' as empty string or left parenthesis or right parenthisis.
It can be done using two stacks:
1. s1=To store the indices of all left parenthisis
2. s2=To store indices all asteric.
We would first try to balance the right parenthisis i.e number of right parenthisis should be less than the number of left parenthisis.
In this case asteric can only behave as empty or left parenthisis.
We would pop an element from s1 everytime we get a right parenthisis.
if the right parenthisis are balanced we would balance the left paranthesis.
This situation will only arise if size of stack s1 is greater than zero.
Now the situation is totally opposite now asteric can behave only as empty or right parentheisis.For every star a left parenthesis will be balanced.
Now here is the catch**We could have also stored the characters in the stack but why did we store the indices?
This is because every right parenthesis occurs after its left parenthesis hence in order to keep a check on their position indices are used**
Consider these situations
*  "****(("
*  "((***"
*  "))***"
*  "*)( *"

Think about this situation yourself
For better understanding the code is available
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool checkValidString(string s) {
        if(s.size()==0)
            return true;
        stack <int> s1;
        stack <int> s2;
        for(int i=0;i<s.size();i++){
            if(s[i]=='(')
                s1.push(i);
            if(s[i]=='*')
                s2.push(i);
            if(s[i]==')'){
                if(s1.size()==0 && s2.size()==0)
                    return false;
                else if(s1.size()==0)
                    s2.pop();
                else
                    s1.pop();
            }
        }
        if(s1.size()==0)
            return true;
        while(s2.size()!=0){
             if(s1.size()==0)
                return true;
            else if(s1.top()<s2.top()){
                s1.pop();
                s2.pop();
            }

            else if(s1.top()>s2.top())
                return false;

        }
        if(s1.size()==0)
        return true;
        else
            return false;

    }
};
```

