I have been mangled with this for much more I expected. So I want to share my solution here.
The basic idea is kept tracking what is the range the result could be. Eventullay the result should be 0. Tricky part is in the procedure, the result should be negative, like "))((" or "*))(". So the first * can't be used as ")".
```
class Solution {
    public boolean checkValidString(String s) {
        int[] range = new int[2];
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            char c = s.charAt(i);
            if (c == '(') {
                range[0]++;
                range[1]++;
            } else if (c == '*') {
                range[0] = Math.max(0, range[0]-1);
                range[1]++;
            } else if (c == ')') {
                range[0] = Math.max(0, range[0]-1);
                range[1]--;
                if (range[1] < 0) {
                    return false;
                }
            }
        }

        return range[0] == 0;
    }
}
```

